Dearest friends, I'm calling on you to lend a paw today with just a minute of your time for a very important cause!

I have all my claws under this glorious floof, but many of my fellow kitties are not so lucky. Declawing is not simply removing nails - it is amputation. This inhumane procedure actually involves cutting off the tips of each finger! Many countries have already banned declawing, but in the United States, it's estimated that 25% of cats are declawed. We need to end this abuse.

I'm joining my friends at Purrfect Pals and The Paw Project in the effort to ban declawing in Washington State. It starts with a petition - enough signatures and we can get this on the ballot for an official vote. Please click the link in my bio, or simply visit the redirect I set up on my website at brimleycat.com/claws to read more about the issue, and sign the petition today!
